headline: If Wall Street CEOs See a Recession, Their Guidance Isn’t Showing It—Yet
summary: JPMorgan Chase Wells Fargo  and  Morgan Stanley  reported solid earnings results, while  BlackRock  posted another quarter of record assets.  In a pleasant surprise for investors—who in some cases were expecting market-sensitive firms to dial down their earnings forecasts—the companies left their outlooks largely unchanged.  Uncertainty abounds.
